# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers per path.
#
# GitHub requests a review from the matching owner(s) on every PR, and (when
# "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled in branch protection) their
# approval is required to merge. Later matches win, so more specific paths
# override the global default.
#
# ⚠️ EDIT THE OWNERS BELOW before enabling. Replace @hackerwins with the real
# maintainer usernames or a team (e.g. @wafflebase/maintainers). Every listed
# owner must have write access to the repo, or GitHub silently ignores the line.
# This file is the human gate for the autonomous agent pipeline: the agent can
# never be a code owner, so a human owner always has to approve.

# Global default owner for everything not matched below.
*                               @hackerwins

# --- Packages (uncomment / assign as ownership solidifies) -------------------
# /packages/sheets/             @hackerwins
# /packages/docs/               @hackerwins
# /packages/slides/             @hackerwins
# /packages/frontend/           @hackerwins
# /packages/backend/            @hackerwins
# /packages/cli/                @hackerwins
# /packages/core/               @hackerwins

# --- Harness / CI / release infrastructure ----------------------------------
/.github/                       @hackerwins
/scripts/                       @hackerwins
/harness.config.json            @hackerwins
/docs/design/harness-engineering.md  @hackerwins

# --- Autonomous agent pipeline (extra scrutiny) ------------------------------
# These files decide what the agent is allowed to do — keep them tightly owned.
/.github/workflows/agent-*.yml  @hackerwins
/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/agent-task.yml  @hackerwins
/scripts/agent/                 @hackerwins
/scripts/hooks/                 @hackerwins
/.claude/                       @hackerwins
